    {
      "title": "Adverbs of Time and Place (ظرف الزمان والمكان)",
      "titleArabic": "ظرف الزمان والمكان",
      "content": [
        "Adverbs of time (ظرف الزمان) and place (ظرف المكان) are nouns that indicate when or where an action occurs. They are always in the accusative case (منصوب).",
        "These adverbs often function as مضاف, with the following noun in the genitive case (مجرور)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Time adverbs: قَبْلَ (before), بَعْدَ (after), عِنْدَ (at the time of)",
        "Place adverbs: فَوْقَ (above), تَحْتَ (below), أَمَامَ (in front of), وَرَاءَ (behind)",
        "Always منصوب (accusative) as adverbs",
        "Followed by مجرور noun when used as مضاف"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "قَبْلَ الدَّرْسِ", "english": "before the lesson" },
        { "arabic": "بَعْدَ الصَّلَاةِ", "english": "after the prayer" },
        { "arabic": "الْكِتَابُ فَوْقَ الطَّاوِلَةِ", "english": "The book is above the table" },
        { "arabic": "جَلَسَ أَمَامَ الْمُدَرِّسِ", "english": "He sat in front of the teacher" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Common Spatial Adverbs",
      "titleArabic": "الظروف المكانية الشائعة",
      "content": [
        "Memorize these commonly used spatial adverbs that indicate position and direction."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "فَوْقَ (above) ↔ تَحْتَ (below)",
        "أَمَامَ (in front of) ↔ وَرَاءَ/خَلْفَ (behind)",
        "يَمِينَ (right of) ↔ يَسَارَ/شِمَالَ (left of)",
        "بَيْنَ (between) - requires two objects"
      ]
    }
  ],
